properties.headline: Gale Warning issued March 1 at 3:46PM EST until March 2 at 5:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and waves
6 to 9 feet expected.

* WHERE...Ontonagon to Upper Entrance of Portage Canal MI, Lake
Superior from Saxon Harbor WI to Upper Entrance to Portage
Canal MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border including
Isle Royale National Park, Black River to Ontonagon MI and
Saxon Harbor WI to Black River MI.

* WHEN...From 9 PM EST /8 PM CST/ this evening to 5 AM EST /4 AM
CST/ Monday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM EST /8 PM CST/ THIS EVENING TO 5 AM EST /4 AM CST/ MONDAY
